assessment_details.task_description:
Word limit: Maximum 4000 words (excluding attachments)

Your team has now progressed to stage 2 of the tender bid process with the client wanting a more detailed research proposal to be submitted for their consideration.

A group research proposal is required to be developed, and should include the following details:

outline of the research team and your suitability for the task;

brief background to the research problem and key literature sources;

identity the issue/gap and define project aims, research questions and/or objectives for the research;

research methodology including the design and proposed data collection methods including sampling;

proposed data analysis techniques to be employed and how the data would be presented;

proposed timeline and milestones;

budget for the work proposed;

reference list; and

attachments including draft survey instruments, personal interview or focus group schedules.

It is expected that your group will integrate and use key concepts and material from the course to support and justify your proposal. In particular, your proposal will need to integrate and use research method texts/articles in the report to justify decisions . It is critical that a concerted effort is made to demonstrate a clear link between the research design, implementation and proposed analysis.

Your proposal should be written in a structured format and follow the sub headings as outlined above. The proposal itself should be detailed enough for a client or researcher to successfully implement the proposal and collect data.

Further information on this assessment task will be discussed in class and posted to your course Blackboard site.
